  "text": "The results with a pure enstrophy cascade, forced in the range K = [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and with no Rayleigh damping (R = 0), are significantly worse (Fig. 12) . The slope in the inertial range is close to, though slightly steeper than, K −3 . However the spectrum from the theoretical S2 (red dotted curve) is accurate only at the smallest wavenumbers. It begins to oscillate around K = 10 and these oscillations increase with wavenumber; the dotted curve indicates the upper branch of the curve, and the lower values are actually negative. The spectrum derived from the polynomial fit (blue dotted curve) deviates from the original spectrum at even smaller wavenumbers, and exhibits negative values even below K = 10. The upper branch mirrors that from the theoretical S2, but the values are roughly 10 times larger. The spectrum from the raw data (green dots) is again poor.",
